 CPU Scaling: Save battery on low-end laptops

 Solutions that i found:

- Frequency Limiting (the'give me only what i need and want'trick):
If your battery is old and his battery is a joke like the second you remove the charger the battery drain like if it was a timer or your pc burns the second you get into you pc here is the fix

Ubuntu / Debian:
1. Install TLP: sudo apt install tlp tlp-rdw
2. Start it: sudo tlp start
3. (Optional) Edit /etc/tlp.conf to set:
   CPU_SCALING_MAX_FREQ_ON_BAT=(write your cpu frequency in hz)
#just for reference 1ghz means 1 and 5 zeros 
